{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:proverbs.2",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 2,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 2 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.2.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:1",
      "text": "My son, if you will receive my words, and store up my commandments within you,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.2.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:2",
      "text": "so as to turn your ear to wisdom, and apply your heart to understanding;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.2.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:3",
      "text": "yes, if you call out for discernment, and lift up your voice for understanding;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.2.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:4",
      "text": "if you seek her as silver, and search for her as for hidden treasures;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.2.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:5",
      "text": "then you will understand the fear of Yahweh, and find the knowledge of God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.2.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:6",
      "text": "For Yahweh gives wisdom. Out of his mouth comes knowledge and understanding.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.2.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:7",
      "text": "He lays up sound wisdom for the upright. He is a shield to those who walk in integrity,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.2.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:8",
      "text": "that he may guard the paths of justice, and preserve the way of his saints.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.2.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:9",
      "text": "Then you will understand righteousness and justice, equity and every good path.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.2.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:10",
      "text": "For wisdom will enter into your heart. Knowledge will be pleasant to your soul.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.2.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:11",
      "text": "Discretion will watch over you. Understanding will keep you,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.2.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:12",
      "text": "to deliver you from the way of evil, from the men who speak perverse things,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.2.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:13",
      "text": "who forsake the paths of uprightness, to walk in the ways of darkness,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.2.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:14",
      "text": "who rejoice to do evil, and delight in the perverseness of evil,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.2.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:15",
      "text": "who are crooked in their ways, and wayward in their paths,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.2.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:16",
      "text": "to deliver you from the strange woman, even from the foreigner who flatters with her words,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.2.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:17",
      "text": "who forsakes the friend of her youth, and forgets the covenant of her God;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.2.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:18",
      "text": "for her house leads down to death, her paths to the departed spirits.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.2.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:19",
      "text": "None who go to her return again, neither do they attain to the paths of life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.2.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:20",
      "text": "Therefore walk in the way of good men, and keep the paths of the righteous.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.2.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:21",
      "text": "For the upright will dwell in the land. The perfect will remain in it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.2.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:22",
      "text": "But the wicked will be cut off from the land. The treacherous will be rooted out of it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
